                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> PUSEY, Berks. <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> de <surname>Sanford</surname>
                        </persName> grants in
               frankalmoigne, to the <orgName key="org_107016">church of St. Mary, St. Nicholas, and St. Edmund, Cherley ('Cerleiam')</orgName>, at the reception there of his daughter,
               certain lands with a mill in his demesne of <placeName key="place_109446">Pusey</placeName>, and also confirms conjointly
               with <persName nymRef="Sanford">
                           <forename>Jordan</forename> his son</persName>, and 
               <persName nymRef="Sanford">
                           <forename>Christiana</forename>, wife</persName> of the said Jordan, whatever
               (8 acres) <persName>
                           <forename>Roger</forename> the <surname type="patronymic">son of Richard</surname>
                        </persName> 
               and Ralph his son gave and will give to the same church, and also gives ten acres on account of the reception of Christina his
               little daughter, "parvule filie", and confirms the gift of 
               <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> the <surname type="patronymic">son of Warner</surname>
                        </persName>. 
               (<origDate notBefore="1150" notAfter="1160" precision="low">c. 1150-60</origDate>.) 
               </p>
